{"id": "duc04-testb-31:3#9", "contents": "Opposition parties lodged no-confidence motions against Prime Minister Mesut Yilmaz on Wednesday following allegations that he interfered in the privatization of a bank and assisted a businessman linked to a notorious mobster. The prime minister's minority government may collapse if the center-left Republican Party, which typically provides Yilmaz with the necessary majority in parliament, decides to vote against him. Republican Party leader Deniz Baykal has called on Yilmaz to resign, citing the severity of the allegations."}
